race.comment: MOGUL MONARCH (2) was there to strike but peaked on his run last start over 1400m at Warwick Farm. Has three wins and two minors from six runs at the trip - the only failure coming on a bog. Can bounce back to form at decent odds. POLYGLOT (7) was snagged back from a wide gate then wound up strongly to grab third behind Monte Supreme in a similar race here a fortnight ago. Again draws poorly but is rock hard fit and must win one sooner or later. ROSELYN'S STAR (3) finished a couple of lengths ahead of POLYGLOT when they met two weeks back. Lightly raced sprinter who should be at his peak for this, although the early price on offer is a but skinny. AMAZING EAGLE (1) last raced 315 days ago. Excellent fresh performer whose recent Warwick Farm trial win suggests he is right on track for this. POKERJACK (9) likes Rosehill and wasn't far away in a comparable race to this three back. Worth a ticket at massive odds.
